docs.snippet: Police detained Uganda's main opposition candidate Kizza Besigye for the third time this week and clashed with his supporters on Friday as early contested election results showed President Yoweri Museveni set to extend his 30-year grip on power....
docs.lead_paragraph: Police detained Uganda's main opposition candidate Kizza Besigye for the third time this week and clashed with his supporters on Friday as early contested election results showed President Yoweri Museveni set to extend his 30-year grip on power.

headline.main: Uganda Detains Opposition Leader Again as President Heads for Vote Win
headline.print_headline: Uganda Detains Opposition Leader Again as President Heads for Vote Win
